# Commit Style

```
<scope>: short imperative title

- bullet describing what changed and why
- another bullet if needed
```

## Rules
- Always in English
- Title: imperative mood, lowercase after the colon, no period
- Scope: the area changed (e.g. `tools`, `arch/tricore`, `kernel`, `ipc`, `docs`, `ci`)
- Body: bullet points, focus on *why* not *what*; omit if title is self-explanatory

## Examples

```
tools: add TriCore dev container and hello world example

- Docker image with GCC 13.4, GDB 14, and linumiz QEMU TC27x
- dev.py script mounts workspace and drops into interactive shell
- tools/hello validates the full compile → QEMU run flow
```

```
arch/tricore: implement CSA free list init in startup

- QEMU resets FCX to 0; any CALL before init causes a silent FCU trap
```
